text: Foteini Andronikou (born 14 March 1994) is a Cypriot footballer who plays as a midfielder and has appeared for the Cyprus women's national team. ==Career== Andronikou has been capped for the Cyprus national team, appearing for the team during the UEFA Women's Euro 2021 qualifying cycle. ==References== ==External links== * * * Category:1994 births Category:Living people Category:Cypriot women's footballers Category:Cyprus women's international footballers Category:Women's association football midfielders Category:Apollon Ladies F.C. players
